list.comment:
Add JSON converters and improve serialization for Currency/Money
Introduce `CurrencyJsonConverter` and enhance `MoneyJsonConverter` to handle serialization/deserialization for both Newtonsoft.Json and System.Text.Json. Updated unit tests and refactored `Currency` struct to optimize internal storage and validation of ISO-4217 codes.

task.summary: Default task
Update Build and moved Benchmarks to seperate project

Add MoneyUnit struct and adjust performance tests
A new struct, MoneyUnit, was added in the NodaMoney namespace that simplifies handling currency and amount. Performance test report has been updated to reflect the changes introduced by this new feature. Some import statements were also adjusted for added functionality.
Merge branch 'feature/improve-performance-class' into feature/improve-performance

Updated .NET5 handling for invariant cultures
This commit adds special handling for invariant cultures in .NET5 or higher. If the current culture is invariant, a specific code is returned instead of attempting to extract region information. This aligns with changes in .NET5 where CurrentRegion is retrieved from Windows settings when CurrentCulture is Invariant. The same check has been added to throw an exception when trying to get a currency from an invariant culture. Minor reordering of lines in the test helper class for clearer code readability.

Skip serialization tests for .NET 8.0 or greater
This commit adds conditional compilation directives to skip certain serialization tests if the target framework is.NET 8.0 or greater. This is due to the fact that these tests use BinaryFormatter, which is not supported in .NET 8.0 or later as per Microsoft's guidance. The Serialize and Deserialize methods have been marked as obsolete.

Added test cases for System.Text.Json serialization and deserialization #98 (still failing)
Added multiple test cases to test serialization and deserialization of the 'Money' object using the System.Text.Json library. The test cases cover both valid and invalid scenarios and also include testing the serialization and deserialization of nested objects.

Added test cases for System.Text.Json serialization and deserialization #98 (still failing)
Added multiple test cases to test serialization and deserialization of the 'Money' object using the System.Text.Json library. The test cases cover both valid and invalid scenarios and also include testing the serialization and deserialization of nested objects.

Updated NodaMoney library to .NET 8 and improved performance
The NodaMoney library has been updated to use .NET 8 and performance has been significantly improved. This includes changes to the CurrencyUnit and Money classes, and the renaming of a method from AssertIsSameCurrency to VerifySameCurrency. The codebase has also been cleaned and unnecessary comments, files, and calls have been removed. The changes have also been reflected in the benchmark and test cases.

This includes changes to the CurrencyUnit and Money classes, and the renaming of a method from AssertIsSameCurrency to VerifySameCurrency. The codebase has also been cleaned and unnecessary comments, files, and calls have been removed. The changes have also been reflected in the benchmark and test cases.

Replace MoneyUnit with FastMoney struct, remove unused using directives
Removed unused "System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis" and "System.Runtime.InteropServices" using directives in CurrencyUnit.cs. Replaced the "MoneyUnit" structure with the more efficient "FastMoney" structure in "FastMoney.cs" and updated all references in HighLoadBenchmarks.cs. The new structure should provide faster execution times for high load situations.

Add IsExternalInit class for compatibility
A new class, IsExternalInit, has been introduced to maintain compatibility across different .NET versions. It corrects the "CS0518: IsExternalInit is not defined" error which was occurring in certain .NET environments.

Add new solution folders
Three new folders - 'workflows', 'src', and 'tests' have been added to the NodaMoney solution. The nested relations between these projects have been defined in the GlobalSection of the solution file.

Improve performance metrics in Testing Report
Modified the PerformanceReport.md file under NodaMoney.Tests. The updated report shows significant improvement in the execution time of various methods

Update project files and code formating

The LICENSE.txt file has been renamed to LICENSE, modifications in .gitignore and .editorconfig files have been made to better suit project requirements, and adjustments in README.md and CONTRIBUTING.md files have been made for clarity and consistency.

Add Sierra Leonean leone to Currency Registry
A new currency, the Sierra Leonean leone (SLE), has been added to the Currency Registry. This updates the registry with the latest currency used in Sierra Leone as of April 2021, replacing the previous SLL/694 currency.

Update handling of CustomDictionary.xml in project file
Moved the reference to `CustomDictionary.xml` from its own `ItemGroup` to an existing one in `NodaMoney.csproj`. The file now has the code analysis dictionary attribute set to true and its newest version is preserved in the output directory. Reference to `CustomDictionary.xml` was also removed from `NodaMoney.sln`.
Updated codebase to use top-level statements and removed unnecessary namespaces

Add CurrencyList and MinorUnit classes; refactor CurrencyUnit
The CurrencyList and MinorUnit enums have been moved into separate classes to improve code organization. In CurrencyUnit, change how minor unit and currency list are stored: keep them in a combined variable named _listAndMinorUnit. These changes make the structure more understandable and easier to maintain.

Refactor code and add newline at end of files
Refactored CurrencyUnit code and removed unnecessary bits from CurrencyUnit's constructor. Added newline character at the end of multiple file to adhere to POSIX standard.
Adjusted code and tests to new Currency and CurrencyInfo
Refactor code to remove unused properties and improve currency handling
CurrencyBuilder marked obsolete, improve serialization

Add JSON support for NodaMoney #98
This commit introduces a new dependency on System.Text.Json. It also adds new code to convert NodaMoney objects to and from JSON. This includes modifications to the NodaMoney.csproj file and the creation of MoneyJsonConverter.cs, which contains the converter implementation.

Refactor and improve serialization and deserialization of Money
This commit refactors and enhances serialization and deserialization of the Money object to handle a wider array of cases and provides better exception handling. It includes modifications in test cases to adapt to new changes, and it also simplifies and cleans up the CurrencyTypeConverter and MoneyTypeConverter classes, adding remarks where necessary.

Delete outdated XML serializer tests and add BinaryFormatter tests
Removed obsolete XML serializer tests for Currency. Added new tests for Money serialization using BinaryFormatter, and cleaned up existing tests by renaming and refactoring for better clarity.

Upgrade to .NET 9 and update package dependencies.
This commit updates the project to target .NET 9.0, enhancing support for the latest platform features. It also includes updates to various package dependencies to their latest versions, ensuring improved performance and compatibility. The GitHub workflows are modified to use .NET 9.0, reflecting these changes across both CI and release processes.

Remove branch specification from CI workflow
The CI workflow now triggers on all branches instead of just 'master' and 'main'. This change allows for more flexibility and ensures that all branches are verified, regardless of their name. Paths under 'docs/**' still do not trigger the workflow.

Enhance JSON Serialization and Deserialization
Updated serialization for `Money` type to support advanced formats, including reversed currency/amount strings. Improved error handling with concise messages for invalid formats. Expanded test coverage for varied JSON serialization scenarios, ensuring robustness with both valid and invalid test cases.

Add IntelliJ IDEA project configuration files
This commit introduces various .idea configuration files for the NodaMoney project. These files include settings for encoding, Git integration, workspace setup, and project-specific configurations to support development within IntelliJ-based IDEs.
